First Read: 17-Feb-26
HJR133 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 NAMING THE BRIDGE ON UNITED STATES HIGHWAY 45 THAT SPANS
4 BENNETT CREEK IN MOBILE COUNTY THE SIDNEY ALDEN HOBBS
5 MEMORIAL BRIDGE.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with the highest accolade that this
8 body honors the memory of Sidney Alden Hobbs by requesting
9 the Department of Transportation designate the bridge on
10 United States Highway 45 that spans Bennett Creek in Mobile
11 County, Alabama, as the Sidney Alden Hobbs Memorial Bridge;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, Sid Hobbs was born March 24, 2008, to John
14 and Elizabeth Hobbs in Citronelle, Alabama; he was a
15 lifelong member of Living Word Church with his siblings and
16 parents where he was active in his youth group; his faith
17 was evident in his kindhearted demeanor and his love for
18 others; and
19 WHEREAS, Sid lived his life to the fullest and,
20 though many others would have found struggle and defeat, Sid
21 remained positive and motivated throughout his many battles
22 with brain cancer; his bright spirit and loving nature
23 continue to inspire his community; with the naming of this
24 bridge in his honor, his legacy of resilience will be
25 remembered for generations to come; now therefore,
26 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
27 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That to honor Sidney Alden Hobbs,
28 who loved his community and was beloved in return, the
Page 1

who loved his community and was beloved in return, the
HJR133 Enrolled
29 Department of Transportation is encouraged to coordinate
30 with local governing officials to consider designating the
31 bridge on United States Highway 45 that spans Bennett Creek
32 in Mobile County the Sidney Alden Hobbs Memorial Bridge and
33 to erect appropriate signs or markers, consistent with
34 applicable requirements and laws, in recognition of this
35 designation.
